<TEXT>
<P>
 Continental Announces New Fare Cuts: Continental Airlines said late Friday 
that the latest cuts will be available today through Friday.Travel is available 
starting Dec. 3 and must be completed by Feb. 15, if within the United States, 
and by March 31 to Europe. Other restrictions also apply. As an example of the 
cuts, Continental said the one-way fare between Los Angeles and Madrid would 
drop to $279 from $379; from San Diego to Atlanta, to $179 from $295. It was 
not known late Friday if other airlines would match the discounts, the latest 
in a series of cuts during the slower winter travel season. 
