BRIEFLY: AUTOS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Chrysler Minivans May Be Recalled: Federal regulators are leaning toward 
asking the auto maker to recall about 4 million of its popular minivans because 
of allegedly unsafe rear door latches, the Detroit News reported.The rear hatch 
doors in Chrysler Corp. minivans have popped open in 51 accidents, with 74 
passengers being thrown out and 25 deaths reported, the government said. NHTSA 
has been investigating the safety of the latches since October, 1993. Critics 
of the minivan, led by attorneys for crash victims, claim the vehicle's rear 
liftgate door is prone to pop open in rear-impact collisions. Chrysler 
spokesman Rick Deneau said the Detroit News' report of a possible recall 
request was "premature." 
</P>
