COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; HOMES NEEDED FOR EXCHANGE STUDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Temporary homes are still needed to house exchange students from Europe, South 
Africa and Russia during the spring semester beginning in January. 
</P>
<P>
 The International Education Forum is looking for host families to volunteer 
their homes for a male or female student 14 to 16 years old. 
</P>
<P>
 Students have their own spending money and insurance. By providing room and 
board for three to 10 months, host families can get 20% off the cost of a 
scholarship for a family member to stay at a home in Spain, France, Russia or 
several other locations. 
</P>
<P>
 For information about joining the International Education Forum program, call 
(714) 362-0810 or (800) 578-2316. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
