COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: BREA; MAINTENANCE DIRECTOR MCCARRON HONORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Patrick McCarron, the city's maintenance service director, has received this 
year's Peter W. Walsh Award in recognition of his 26 years of service in 
municipal government. 
</P>
<P>
 The award was presented by the Maintenance Superintendents Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The association's executive board recently singled out McCarron from the 
organization's 1,500 members in California and Nevada. 
</P>
<P>
 McCarron has been a Brea city employee for 21 years. 
</P>
<P>
 Before that, he worked five years with the City of Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 The Walsh Award, a bronze sculpture that depicts various aspects of 
maintenance work, will be on display at the Brea Civic & Cultural Center for 
one year. ALAN EYERLY 
</P>
