</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County Supervisor Harriett M. Wieder has presented two checks worth 
$239,000 to the City Council to pay for improvements to some of the city's 
parks. 
</P>
<P>
 A $200,000 grant from the county's Urban Parks program will be used to add 
lighting and other improvements to the athletic field of McAuliffe Middle 
School.The city also received a $39,000 grant to buy playground equipment at 
Labourdette, Sterns, Soroptomist, Roberts and Little Cottonwood parks. 
</P>
<P>
 "We're particularly glad to see you when you bring money," Mayor Anthony R. 
Selvaggi jokingly told Wieder, who is retiring after 16 years on the Board of 
Supervisors. 
</P>
<P>
 The council presented Wieder with a proclamation honoring her for her work as 
supervisor representing the 2nd District, which includes Los Alamitos. BERT 
ELJERA 
