</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Sheriff's deputies on Friday arrested an Aliso Viejo man who shot at a fellow 
gang member and missed outside a Laguna Niguel restaurant, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Thadeus Smith, 32, was booked into Orange County Jail on suspicion of assault 
with a deadly weapon in connection with the shooting, which took place after a 
fistfight with the victim, said Sheriff's Lt. William Francis.He was being held 
on $50,000 bail, according to jail officials. 
</P>
