<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Harry Noonan runs one of the oldest Christmas Tree lots in Orange County. 
</P>
<P>
 Since 1944, Noonan has been selling trees during the holiday season at 
locations around Costa Mesa. He and his son now run the business out of a lot 
in the 2100 block of Newport Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 When he started out, Noonan sold trees for 25 cents. Many of his customers 
then were farmers in the agricultural area known as Goat Hill. 
</P>
<P>
 Now, trees sell anywhere from $19 to $2,000, the family said. 
</P>
<P>
 Noonan has been forced to move his business several times as Costa Mesa's open 
spaces were developed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
