<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: MISSION VIEJO; COMMISSIONERS OK PLANS FOR REI STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission this week approved a 35,000-square-foot retail store 
at the Freeway Center shopping mall. 
</P>
<P>
 By a 4-0 vote, commissioners granted a request from the Mission Viejo Co. to 
cancel plans for a restaurant in the mall and add the square footage to another 
commercial space to make way for a larger retail store. 
</P>
<P>
 REI Inc., a chain of stores selling rock-climbing equipment and other outdoors 
goods, will be moving into the new building. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners were so enthused about having REI in the city that they asked 
company representatives if they wanted more sign space. 
</P>
<P>
 "We are usually stingy about handing out sign space," Commissioner Sunnie 
Castner said. "But we thought people driving south (on El Paseo) needed the 
sign to recognize the building." 
</P>
<P>
 The company said it hopes to have the store open by June. 
</P>
<P>
 The only objection to the sporting goods store came from the city of Laguna 
Hills, which asked for shorter store hours. 
</P>
<P>
 The commission declined the request. "The current hours set in the list of 
conditions (for the proposed REI store) are fine," Castner said. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to selling goods for mountaineers, REI will also build a climbing 
wall where customers can try out their equipment. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
