<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES; 3 KILLED, 
SEVERAL INJURED IN 2 HOLIDAY ACCIDENTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three men were killed and several people were injured in two accidents 
apparently involving drunk drivers Thursday night and early Friday. Two drivers 
were in custody, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 About 2:45 a.m. Friday, a collision between two cars on Sunset Boulevard at 
McCadden Place in Hollywood left one driver dead, the other driver in custody 
suspected of drunk driving and a passenger in the suspect's car critically 
injured. 
</P>
<P>
 Sergio Marcial, 23, was booked for "vehicular manslaughter while driving under 
the influence of alcohol," said Los Angeles Police Officer P. Bartlett of the 
West Traffic Division. Marcial suffered a minor injury. 
</P>
<P>
 The other driver, a 22-year-old man, died at Cedars-Sinai Medical Center three 
hours after the crash, Bartlett said. His name was being withheld pending 
notification of relatives. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger in Marcial's car was in critical condition at the same hospital, 
being treated for "massive head and body trauma," Bartlett said. The name of 
the man was not released. Marcial and the fatally injured driver apparently had 
been involved in a traffic dispute, Bartlett said. 
</P>
<P>
 Shortly after 11 p.m. Thursday, two cars crashed head-on on Sunset Boulevard 
near Edgecliffe Drive in Silver Lake when one car crossed the center line. 
</P>
<P>
 A car carrying three people, heading east on Sunset with its headlights off, 
crossed onto the wrong side of the street and hit a westbound car occupied by 
two people, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 A passenger in the second car, Jack Zinder, 33, of Los Angeles died at the 
scene. An unidentified 24-year-old man riding in the first car died at a 
hospital, police said. Zinder was a music critic for the L.A. Weekly newspaper. 
</P>
<P>
 The others, including both drivers, were critically injured. The driver of the 
first car faces a possible drunk driving charge, police said. His name has not 
been released. 
</P>
