<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; A YEAR WITHOUT HOT DOGS IS ENDING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a year of closed concession stands at Simi Valley parks, residents will 
once again be able to purchase hot dogs and sodas at softball games, park 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rancho Simi Recreation and Park District recently signed a five-year 
contract with Nizar Patel, owner of Shakey's Pizza in Mountaingate Plaza, to 
operate and improve two snack bars on park district property. 
</P>
<P>
 The stands are near softball diamonds at Rancho Simi Community Park and Rancho 
Santa Susana Community Park. 
</P>
<P>
 Poor sales prompted the previous operator to close last year, district board 
member James Meredith said. 
</P>
<P>
 "This is a good deal, I think," Meredith said. "It's convenient for people in 
the park to be able to get hot drinks on a cold night or cold drinks on a hot 
night." 
</P>
<P>
 Patel's contract begins Jan. 1. After he makes some improvements, the stands 
will be open on a regular basis during evening sports league games and on the 
weekends. Patel said he will sell hot dogs, cold sandwiches, chips, sodas, 
pretzels and ice cream. MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</TEXT>
