<HEADLINE>
<P>
'REJECTION DAY' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I am very pleased, rather I should say very happy, that the elections are 
over.I'm sure there are millions of others that agree with me and for the same 
reason. 
</P>
<P>
 These so-called candidates running for office hardly ever tell you what they 
can do or what they will try to do for us. All they do is smear each other. 
Truthfully, it's sickening. 
</P>
<P>
 I don't know, maybe it's me. Maybe it's the way I think. Why can't they speak 
about themselves? 
</P>
<P>
 Maybe we should call it Rejection Day instead of Election Day and vote to 
reject the one with the worse reputation. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM FOX, Camarillo 
</P>
