<HEADLINE>
<P>
FOR SECOND CHANCES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I can understand the frustration and fear that the teachers are feeling about 
students carrying weapons on campus in Moorpark. 
</P>
<P>
 Having taught school for 25 years for the Los Angeles Unified School District, 
I did not experience the violent encounters they have had.I retired in 1985, 
having taught in Woodland Hills among, for the most part, well-mannered pupils. 
</P>
<P>
 I believe everyone, especially youngsters, should be given a second chance. I 
am not condoning their carrying a weapon on campus, but I feel that expulsion 
is too drastic. 
</P>
<P>
 Instead, I would strongly recommend a one-year suspension, with the 
understanding that the youngster stay out of trouble during that time and then 
be reinstated in school. 
</P>
<P>
 I believe giving the child a second chance would give him (or her) time to 
contemplate and feel the loss of not being with his friends. 
</P>
<P>
 LILLIAN RAE, Oxnard Shores 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Letter to the Editor 
