<HEADLINE>
<P>
THOUSAND OAKS CHASES DOUBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks High will try to record its second historic double in eight days 
when the CIF State cross-country championships are held today at Fresno's 
Woodward Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The Lancers won the boys' and girls' Division I titles in last week's Southern 
Section championships at Mt. San Antonio College in Walnut, becoming the first 
program to sweep both major-division titles in the same year. 
</P>
<P>
 This morning, they are expected to become the first program to win both 
Division I state titles in the same meet. 
</P>
<P>
 The Thousand Oaks boys, third in The Harrier magazine's national poll, are 
heavy favorites. JOHN ORTEGA 
</P>
</TEXT>
