<HEADLINE>
<P>
MATER DEI DEFEATS LOYOLA, 31-7 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MICHAEL ITAGAKI, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mater Dei posted a decisive 31-7 victory over Los Angeles Loyola in a Southern 
Section Division I quarterfinal football game Friday night at Cerritos College. 
</P>
<P>
 No. 3-ranked Mater Dei (12-0) advanced to the semifinals to play No. 2 Los 
Alamitos, a 7-0 winner over Long Beach Poly. 
</P>
<P>
 After the Monarchs started slowly, a crowd of 7,500 watched Mater Dei dominate 
Loyola. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei running back Steve Bodnar rushed for 102 yards in 20 carries, and 
also scored a touchdown. Fullback Joey Trampush scored two touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 Mater Dei quarterback John Flynn completed 12 of 19 passes for 228 yards with 
a touchdown and an interception. Wide receiver Rod Perry caught three passes 
for 107 yards and a touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Defensively, the Monarchs limited the Cubs (8-3) to 73 yards in the first half 
as they built a 17-0 lead. Cornerback Kevin Braga intercepted two passes for 
Mater Dei, which held Loyola to three second-half first downs. 
</P>
<P>
 Loyola's longest play from scrimmage came late in the fourth quarter when 
guard Robert Quigley ran for 47 yards on a "fumblerooski" play. But for the 
most part, the Monarchs kept Loyola in check. 
</P>
<P>
 "Mater Dei is a physical team," Loyola Coach Steve Grady said. "They have the 
size up front, and the talent at the skill positions . . . that combination is 
tough to beat." 
</P>
<P>
 Flynn cashed in Braga's first interception, moving the Monarchs 84 yards in 
five plays for a score with less than five minutes remaining in the second 
quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 A 49-yard bomb from Flynn to Perry moved Mater Dei deep into Loyola territory, 
and Perry capped the drive when he split two Loyola defenders on a post pattern 
and Flynn found him for a 21-yard touchdown pass play with 1:43 left in the 
half and a 17-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 "I thought our pass defense was one of our strengths," Grady said. "But 
(Flynn) kept making the big pass play against us." 
</P>
<P>
 Mike Vanis tried to help the Cubs bounce back in the second half. After 
quarterback Kyle Spielbuehler connected with Dan Farmer for a 39-yard pass 
play, Vanis scored on a three-yard touchdown run one play later to make it 17-7 
with 5:17 remaining in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 But the Monarchs responded with a 12-play drive covering 75 yards, with 
Trampush scoring on a one-yard run with one second remaining in the third 
quarter to make it 24-7. 
</P>
</TEXT>
