<P>
UCLA WOMEN LOSE OPENER, 58-55 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The UCLA women's basketball team lost its season opener to North Carolina 
State, 58-55, Friday night at UCLA. 
</P>
<P>
 The Bruins had a chance to send the game into overtime, but Ricarda Kuypers' 
three-pointer from the top of the key fell short at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
 Kellie Bennett led the Bruins with 13 points and seven rebounds. 
</P>
