<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS; TOP OLDER HORSES VIE FOR CHAMPIONS BERTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tonight's $20,000 Z. Wayne Griffin Directors Trial will feature nine of the 
top older horses at Los Alamitos vying for the remaining two spots in the 
Champion of Champions. The top two finishers in the Directors Trial will earn 
berths to the Champion of Champions, to be held Dec. 17 at Los Alamitos. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the top contenders in tonight's trial is Heza Fast Man, a 3-year-old 
colt trained by John Bassett for San Tan Tillage, Inc. Heza Fast Man recently 
won the Vandy's Flash Handicap at Los Alamitos, and previously finished second 
in both the All American Futurity and Derby. He has a career record of ten wins 
from 15 starts. Regular rider Henry Garcia will be aboard in the trial. 
</P>
<P>
 Including Heza Fast Man, a field of nine will go in the Directors Trial. Also 
entered are Seals, Childish, Pritzi Dash, Ima Killer Yawl, Femmes Frolic, 
Sticky N Picky, Angry Angel and Ronas Deal.  
</P>
<P>
 Horses that have already earned berths to the Champion of Champions: 
Refrigerator, Sound Dash, Down With Debt, Avison, I Hear A Symphony, Specially 
Fast, Sheza First Down and Brotherly. STACY PIGOTT 
</P>
