<HEADLINE>
<P>
TWO COUNTY TEAMS VIE FOR SOCCER BERTHS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Cypress women's team and the Rancho Santiago men's team will play today 
for berths in the State soccer tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Cypress (18-0-2) plays host to Moorpark (9-3-4) at 1 p.m. Cypress has 
outscored opponents, 73-3, this season. Tracy Van Herk has 17 assists this 
season for the Chargers and 29 in her career. Carlye Wind has 11 goals for the 
Chargers and Traci Osman and Pam Prine have nine each. 
</P>
<P>
 Glendale is at Rancho Santiago (16-2-3) in a 1 p.m. game. Rancho Santiago is 
led by Francisco Islas, the most valuable player of the Orange Empire 
Conference. 
</P>
<P>
 The winners advance to the State tournament, Dec. 3-4 at Consumnes River 
College in Sacramento. 
</P>
