<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; LUPPANI SETS RECORD IN ORANGE COAST VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Flo Luppani set an Orange Coast College single-game record for assists with 15 
as the Pirates beat Foothill, 87-78, in a nonconference women's basketball game 
Friday at OCC. 
</P>
<P>
 Amierca Robledo and Stephanie McNamara each scored 22 points for OCC 
(5-1).McNamara made 10 of 17 shots and Robledo made nine of 16. 
</P>
<P>
 Jamie Shine added 15 points, making seven of 13 shots. The Pirates shot 52% 
(37 of 71) from the field. Luppani finished with four points. 
</P>
<P>
 Foothill (4-2) plays today at 5 p.m. at Golden West. 
</P>
<P>
 In another nonconference women's game: 
</P>
<P>
 College of Sequoias 66, Golden West 64 -- Shancya Harris was the difference in 
Sequoias' victory, scoring a game-high 23 points and snapping Golden West's 
69-game home-court winning streak. 
</P>
<P>
 Julie Murdent had 18 points for Golden West (4-2). Deana Itow added 14 points, 
and Farrah Magee had 20 rebounds. Sequoias is 6-0. 
</P>
<P>
 In the Utah Valley State men's tournament: 
</P>
<P>
 Utah Valley State 103, Irvine Valley 74 -- Jeremy Garrett scored 19 points in 
Irvine Valley's loss. Teammate Antoine James added 14 points and nine rebounds, 
and Rashad Wilson scored 13 points. 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine Valley (3-2) is playing without freshman Keon Clark, the 6-foot-11 
center who has a severely sprained ankle and is expected to return in four 
weeks. Utah Valley is 9-1. 
</P>
</TEXT>
