<HEADLINE>
<P>
RANCHO SANTIAGO SWEEPS TOP AWARDS; FOOTBALL: FUENTES, HOLMES ARE PLAYERS OF THE 
YEAR. OGAS IS COACH OF THE YEAR IN THE DIVISION. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rancho Santiago quarterback Simon Fuentes and defensive back Andre Holmes were 
selected as players of the year in a vote of Mission Conference Central 
Division coaches. 
</P>
<P>
 The Dons' Dave Ogas was selected as coach of the year. Rancho Santiago (9-1) 
won the Central Division with a 5-0 mark and will play Los Angeles Valley (9-1) 
in the Simple Green Orange County Bowl Dec. 3 at Orange Coast College. 
</P>
<P>
 Fuentes, a sophomore from Garden Grove High, set a Rancho Santiago 
single-season record with 19 touchdown passes. The Dons had eight players on 
the first team. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton, which finished second in the division, had seven first-team 
players, led by sophomore linebackers Chris Garza and Jason Nevadomsky. The 
Hornets play Hancock College in the K-Swiss Bowl Dec. 3 in Santa Maria. MISSION 
CONFERENCE / CENTRAL DIVISION 
</P>
<P>
 MVP -- Simon Fuentes (Rancho Santiago), QB, So.; Andre Holmes (Rancho 
Santiago), DB, Fr. 
</P>
