<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: NOE OUSTED IN JUNIOR GOLF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Terry Noe of Fullerton won in the first round of match play but lost in the 
second at the Rolex Junior Golf Classic at the par-72 La Paloma Country Club 
courses in Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Noe, the reigning U.S. Junior champion, beat Joel Kribel of Pleasanton, 5 and 
4, but lost to Ryuki Imada of Tampa, Fla., 4 and 2. 
</P>
<P>
 Keri Cornelius of Scottsdale, Ariz., beat Jenny Lee of Fullerton, 4 and 3, in 
the first round of the girls' division. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Nina Vaughan of Corona del Mar High advanced to the round of 16 of the 
national girls' 14s indoor tennis tournament in St. Louis. She defeated Anne 
Nguyen of Lancaster, Pa., 6-1, 6-4. 
</P>
