<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: PACOIMA; YOUTH CENTER GIVEN COMPUTER GRANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TIM MAY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Pacoima Youth Culture Center received a $10,000 grant this week to create 
a computer learning center. 
</P>
<P>
 The funds came from the United Parcel Service Foundation, the charity branch 
of the packaging and delivery service. The youth center, established in 1977, 
provides comprehensive social services to the communities of the northeast San 
Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The computer learning center will feature a jobs databank, an information 
referral network and computer training courses. 
</P>
<P>
 The grant is part of a nationwide program begun by UPS in 1984, which reported 
giving last year a total of $2.5 million to community organizations for 
education, human welfare, adult literacy and food distribution. TIM MAY 
</P>
