<HEADLINE>
<P>
1,600 LEFT IN DARK BY POWER OUTAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOSH MEYER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A power outage Friday night blacked out about 1,600 Department of Water and 
Power customers in the west San Fernando Valley, DWP officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The outage first cut off power at 6:25 p.m. Service was restored, but the 
power failed again soon afterward and stayed off for several hours, said DWP 
spokeswoman Dorothy Jensen. 
</P>
<P>
 She said DWP workers were trying to determine the cause of the outage Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
 No hospitals or other large public facilities were affected, Jensen said. 
</P>
<P>
 The outage was centered in two areas of Northridge and Chatsworth: near the 
intersection of Tulsa Street and Baton Rouge Avenue, and around the corner of 
Devonshire Street and Corbin Avenue, Jensen said. JOSH MEYER 
</P>
</TEXT>
