<HEADLINE>
<P>
RELIGION NOTES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN DART 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CAROL LAWRENCE: A musical and dramatic production, "Someone Special," will be 
presented by singer Carol Lawrence on four evenings beginning Dec. 4 at Church 
on the Way in Van Nuys. 
</P>
<P>
 Lawrence, a veteran of Broadway and television, is a member of the 
congregation. Her performances will follow the church's annual Christmas 
fireside dinners, for which reservations are required. 
</P>
<P>
 For those not attending the dinners, seating will begin 15 minutes before each 
performance at 6:30 p.m. Dec. 4 and 8 p.m. Dec. 5-7. Reservations are not 
required for the musical program at the church, located at 14300 Sherman Way. 
Call (818) 779-8000. 
</P>
<P>
 EDIE ADAMS: Singer and TV personality Edie Adams will host two performances 
Dec. 4 of the annual Christmas concert by the Metropolitan Community Church in 
the Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 The concerts, at 5 and 8 p.m., will feature 40 singers and 20 
instrumentalists, said Steven Applegate, music director for the congregation in 
North Hollywood. 
</P>
<P>
 The shows will be presented at Church of the Valley, 14602 Kittridge Ave., Van 
Nuys. A $10 donation will be asked for non-reserved seating. A limited number 
of reserved seats are available for $50. Call (818) 762-1133. 
</P>
<P>
 HANUKKAH CEREMONY: A community Hanukkah menorah-lighting ceremony, including 
the singing of traditional holiday songs, will be held at 7 p.m. Sunday at 
Congregation Beth Shalom, 23045 Lyons Ave., Santa Clarita. 
</P>
<P>
 Refreshments will be served following the program. More information: (805) 
254-2411. 
</P>
<P>
 CLERGY FORUM: Holy Cross Medical Center in Mission Hills will conduct an 
educational seminar Wednesday on new heart treatments, the psychological 
effects of cardiac disease and family considerations connected with bypass 
surgery. 
</P>
<P>
 Priests and ministers interested in attending the forum, "The Pastoral 
Response to Cardiac Disease," should contact Sister Colleen Settles at (818) 
898-4604. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum is co-sponsored by the chaplaincy services and the parish nurse 
partnership based at the medical center, 15031 Rinaldi St. 
</P>
<P>
 BLAZER TALK: Phil Blazer, publisher of the Valley-based International Jewish 
News and host of his own local radio and television programs, will speak Friday 
night at the Verdugo Hills Hebrew Center in Tujunga. 
</P>
<P>
 Blazer will talk about the current state of Arab-Palestinian-Israeli affairs 
after the regular Friday night service conducted by Rabbi Manny Goldstein. The 
center is at 10275 Tujunga Canyon Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 For reservations, call (818) 352-3171. JOHN DART 
</P>
</TEXT>
