<HEADLINE>
<P>
HARVARD TURNS TO LEMKIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAMES TEMMEL, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After Harvard-Westlake High lost standout running back Abed Abusaleh to a 
shoulder injury in the first quarter, quarterback Derek Lemkin took control of 
the offense and led the Wolverines into the semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
 Lemkin completed seven of 10 passes for 154 yards and three touchdowns as 
Harvard (10-1-1) defeated host St. Joseph in a Southern Section Division IX 
quarterfinal game Friday night.In the semifinals next Friday, Harvard will play 
Atascadero. 
</P>
<P>
 "He put two or three passes right on the money," Harvard Coach Dave Bennett 
said of Lemkin. "He's all heart." 
</P>
<P>
 Lemkin connected with receiver Kadar Lewis on scoring pass plays of 69 and 17 
yards. Lewis finished with four receptions for 114 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Lemkin also threw a 15-yard scoring pass to Lew Roberts. Running back Merlin 
De Martinis had 56 yards in 22 carries. 
</P>
<P>
 Lemkin helped Harvard build a 23-7 lead, but St. Joseph cut the lead to 23-21 
when fullback Steve Kapphahn scored on a one-yard run with 6 minutes 15 seconds 
left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 The Wolverines recovered the onside kick, then took more than four minutes off 
the clock. 
</P>
<P>
 St. Joseph (8-4) took over at its 23-yard line with 1:47 left, but threw four 
consecutive incomplete passes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
