<HEADLINE>
<P>
KILPATRICK AVENGES LOSS TO VALLEY CHRISTIAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RON STAPP, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Senior tailback Mario Qualls rushed for 134 yards and three touchdowns in 17 
carries Friday as Kilpatrick avenged an early-season loss to Cerritos Valley 
Christian with a 33-14 victory in a Southern Section Division X quarterfinal at 
Kennedy High. 
</P>
<P>
 Qualls scored on runs of two, 19 and nine yards, the last giving Kilpatrick 
(10-2) a 26-0 lead in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick will face Montclair Prep in a semifinal next Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Valley Christian (9-3) played without sophomore starting quarterback Kirk 
Saarloos, who suffered a possible broken leg while playing defensive back 
during the Mustangs' opening drive. 
</P>
<P>
 Saarloos' replacement, senior Jon Lee, completed 12 of 24 passes for 135 yards 
and one touchdown. 
</P>
<P>
 Lee hit Trevor Hesner with a three-yard scoring pass to cut the deficit to 
26-7 midway through the fourth quarter, but Edward Lyde followed up with an 
82-yard return for a score on the ensuing kickoff. 
</P>
<P>
 Kilpatrick fullback Gildardo Hernandez gained 94 yards in 13 carries. 
</P>
