<P>
ANDERSON'S 424 YARDS PROPEL MOUNTIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DARIN ESPER, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Montclair Prep's Akil Anderson certainly isn't feeling any effects from the 
knee injury or concussions that slowed him this season. 
</P>
<P>
 After posting a 231-yard rushing performance last week, the junior tailback 
exploded for 424 yards and four touchdowns to lead Montclair Prep's 50-8 rout 
of Big Bear in a Division X quarterfinal Friday night at Valley College. 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair Prep (9-1) will play Kilpatrick in a semifinal Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Anderson, who had 125 yards and a touchdown in nine carries by the end of the 
first quarter, had runs of 11, 12, 14 and 52 yards nullified by penalties. 
</P>
<P>
 "After tonight's performance, I'm sure I'm 100%," said Anderson, who had 41 
carries and scored on runs of one, two, two and three yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Demetris Green (one-yard run), Siggy Jackson (six-yard run) and Rashawn Jones 
(40-yard interception return) also scored for the Mounties. 
</P>
<P>
 Montclair Prep limited Big Bear (8-3-1) to 112 yards. 
</P>
