<HEADLINE>
<P>
QUARTZ HILL STOPS PARAMOUNT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE GALLUZZO, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Quartz Hill High Coach John Albee told his team to make each opponent work for 
every yard. 
</P>
<P>
 That's just what the Rebels did, posting a convincing 21-3 victory over 
Paramount in a Southern Section Division II quarterfinal on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 In next Saturday's semifinals, Quartz Hill will play Hart at College of the 
Canyons. 
</P>
<P>
 Tailback Jeremiah Harris rushed for 197 yards and two touchdowns in 15 
carries, including a 20-yard scoring run that put Quartz Hill (7-3-2) ahead, 
14-0, in the second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 With no score in the first quarter, quarterback Michael Fletcher of Paramount 
(9-3) threw into the end zone for wide receiver David Trotter, but his pass hit 
Rebel cornerback Monte Reed in the back of the helmet. No face-guarding penalty 
was called. 
</P>
<P>
 Two plays later, Harris ran 82 yards to the Pirate four-yard line, setting up 
a five-yard run by quarterback Damein Kendrid. 
</P>
<P>
 Harris closed out the scoring with a 29-yard run late in the fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 Kendrid rushed for 68 yards and completed three of six passes for 29 yards. 
</P>
