<HEADLINE>
<P>
FAITH BAPTIST DRAWS REMATCH FOR 8-MAN TITLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The regular season and playoffs apparently served as nothing more than a 
formality for the eight-man football teams at Faith Baptist and Brentwood 
highs. 
</P>
<P>
 For the second year in a row, the Delphic League foes will meet for the 
Southern Section championship, playing today at 1 p.m. at Brentwood. 
</P>
<P>
 Faith Baptist (9-1) would love to hand Brentwood (10-0) its first defeat of 
the season and avenge two consecutive losses to the Eagles, including a defeat 
in last year's title game. 
</P>
<P>
 Earlier this season, Brentwood beat Faith Baptist, 34-18, after leading, 34-0. 
</P>
<P>
 But quarterback Judd Granzow has Faith Baptist's offense rolling. Faith 
Baptist beat Lone Pine, 52-0, in a semifinal last week with Granzow throwing 
three touchdown passes and running for two more in just one-half of play. 
</P>
<P>
 The game was called because one team led by more than 45 points at halftime. 
BRYAN RODGERS 
</P>
</TEXT>
