<HEADLINE>
<P>
VENTURA COLLEGE BASKETBALL TOURNAMENT; MOORPARK KEEPS HEAD ABOVE WATER, 57-50 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FERNANDO DOMINGUEZ, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 On a night when one of the Twin Towers wobbled, the other stood firm and 
helped Moorpark College defeat Kings River, 57-50, Friday night in a 
first-round game of the Ventura men's basketball tournament. 
</P>
<P>
 Nick Foster scored 15 points and grabbed 14 rebounds for Moorpark (3-1) but 
his twin brother, Paul, managed only two points and eight rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6-foot-8 forwards each scored in double figures in the Raiders' previous 
three games. 
</P>
<P>
 Sophomore guard David Fennel picked up the slack and scored 19 points for 
Moorpark, sinking three three-point baskets. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Kings River) really packed it in (defensively)," said Al Nordquist, Moorpark 
coach. "They weren't going to give up anything inside. . . . (Fennel) hit those 
threes when we needed them." 
</P>
<P>
 Moorpark led, 25-10, in the first half but had to hang on for the victory when 
Kings River (1-3) scored six consecutive points to pull to within 53-49 with 1 
minute 12 seconds left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Point guard Jaime Jaquez had 10 points for Moorpark, which will play Antelope 
Valley in the semifinals tonight at 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Maurice Blanding had nine points for Kings River. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura 132, Compton 58 -- The Pirates (4-0) opened defense of their 
tournament with a blowout victory.  
</P>
<P>
 Ventura, ranked sixth in the state, has scored 100 or more points in every 
game this season. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pirates toyed with Compton (0-3) and dazzled the crowd with no-look 
passes, dunks and behind-the-back passes. Eight Pirates scored in double 
digits, including Gerald Zimmerman who had a game-high 17 points.  
</P>
<P>
 Charles Woodard had 16 points for Ventura and Hakeen Ward added 15. 
</P>
<P>
 Samuel Reese led Compton with 12 points and teammate Marquis Slemmons had 11. 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura will face Santa Barbara in the semifinals tonight at 8. The Vaqueros 
defeated Contra Costa, 79-61. 
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley 86, Hancock 74 -- The Marauders (3-3) rallied behind guards 
Orville Turner and Brandon McIntire. 
</P>
<P>
 Turner scored 29 points and McIntire had 18. Turner also had 11 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 The Marauders shot 57% from the field (28 of 49) and 71% from the free-throw 
line (20 of 28). 
</P>
<P>
 Guard Kenny Evans scored 19 points for Hancock (2-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
