<HEADLINE>
<P>
1994-95 BOYS' BASKETBALL: PACIFIC COAST LEAGUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Costa Mesa 1993-94 RECORDS 
</P>
<P>
 OVERALL: 6-18 
</P>
<P>
 LEAGUE: 0-10 COACH: Jason Ferguson 
</P>
<P>
 RECORD AT SCHOOL: 0-0 04,20,05,06,04 RETURNING STARTERS YR. HGT. P Mike 
Freeman Sr. 6-2 F 04,15,05,06,04 TOP RETURNERS YR. HGT. P Mike Montoya Jr. 5-9 
G Donny Ogo Jr. 5-6 G Josh Weeks Jr. 5-10 G 04,18,05,06,05 TOP NEWCOMERS YR. 
HGT. P Terry Carmon Sr. 6-1 G Charles Chatman Sr. 5-8 G Dewayne Crenshaw Sr. 
6-1 F Bryan Leahy So. 6-4 F Brian Reeves Jr. 5-11 G/F OUTLOOK 
</P>
<P>
 Costa Mesa has won only three league games in three seasons, but Ferguson, at 
23 the youngest head coach in the county, is a voice of optimism. "We believe 
we are a playoff-bound team," he said. "A lot of coaches told me this is the 
worst place for a coach to be--a coach's graveyard. But I look at it the other 
way, that this is the best place for me to be. I've got great kids with a great 
work ethic." Because the Mustangs won't be very tall, Ferguson is emphasizing 
pressure defense. Freeman is the best rebounder and is a good low-post 
defender. Carmon, a transfer from Tustin, is an "unbelievable defender," 
Ferguson said. Ogo, the point guard, is also a strong defender. Ferguson 
believes Weeks, the team's best all-around player, and Montoya could be among 
the county's 10-best three-point shooters. More toughness will be added by 
Crenshaw, Chatman and Reeves, who played for the football team. Crenshaw, in 
particular, will challenge for a starting spot. 
</P>
